WEBVTT

00:03.509 --> 00:06.429
All right,
I have turned "it" into "ziti",

00:07.074 --> 00:10.548
with a triple letter on Z
and a double word on the I.

00:10.673 --> 00:12.934
Plus, going down, I've created "za".

00:15.472 --> 00:16.475
Za?

00:16.560 --> 00:18.365
A colloquialism for pizza.

00:19.417 --> 00:22.973
One of five two-letter words accepted
by the National Scrabble Association.

00:24.794 --> 00:25.797
Unbelievable.

00:25.944 --> 00:27.699
You can call them if you want.

00:29.853 --> 00:32.922
That's what we in Scrabble circles
call a two tile takedown.

00:36.094 --> 00:37.611
Alan, is our limo here yet?

00:37.737 --> 00:39.267
Sorry, I haven't seen a limo.

00:39.392 --> 00:40.645
Oh, 100 points!

00:43.772 --> 00:45.389
That's a gorgeous dress, Courtney.

00:45.558 --> 00:48.462
Thanks. Charlie insisted
on buying it for me to wear tonight.

00:48.588 --> 00:51.463
- What's the charity again?
- I don't know. Landmines, orphans.

00:51.589 --> 00:53.193
Landmines for orphans.

00:53.545 --> 00:55.408
I just want to show you off.

00:56.107 --> 00:58.186
- Well, you look great.
- Thank you.

00:59.237 --> 01:00.440
No, there's...

01:01.232 --> 01:02.535
Something wrong.

01:03.080 --> 01:04.081
What?

01:04.289 --> 01:06.194
I don't know. Something's...

01:06.319 --> 01:07.473
Something's missing.

01:07.925 --> 01:08.927
I got it.

01:14.212 --> 01:15.666
You shouldn't have.

01:16.755 --> 01:19.542
Well, you've done a lot of things for me
you shouldn't have.

01:22.382 --> 01:23.613
Now you look great.

01:23.823 --> 01:25.335
God, it is beautiful.

01:26.138 --> 01:27.141
Thank you.

